  - (b) The following instruments and equipment must not be included in an MEL—(1) Instruments and equipment that are either specifically or otherwise required by the
airworthiness requirements under which the aircraft is type certificated and which are essential for safe operations under all operating conditions.;(2) Instruments and equipment required by an airworthiness directive (AD) to be in operable condition unless the AD provides otherwise.;(3) Instruments and equipment required for specific operations by this part.;
